{"owner_org": "9391E0A2-9717-4755-B548-4499C21F917B", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "Rapport n\u00b0 2, Direction g\u00e9n\u00e9rale des terres, Environnement Canada, 1972. u093n", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\u00e9o", "title_fra": "Inventaire des terres du Canada (1/250 000) - Possibilit\u00e9s des terres pour la faune - ongul\u00e9s - u093n", "keywords": "Animals,Game (wildlife),Soil,Ungulates,Soils,Soil compaction,Soil consistence,Soil fertility,Soil heat budget,Soil horizons - profile,Soil structure,Soil texture,Vegetation,Biomass,Indigenous vegetation,Land use - land cover,Land management", "data_series_issue_identification": "Report No.2, Lands Directorate, Environment Canada, 1972. u093n", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Inventaire des terres du Canada (1/250 000) - Possibilit\u00e9s des terres pour la faune - ongul\u00e9s", "spatial_representation_type": "Vector | Vecteur", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "geoginfo@NRCan.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "La cartographie des propri\u00e9t\u00e9s physiques des terres qui les rendent propres \u00e0 servir d'habitat aux ongul\u00e9s est \u00e9tablie dans le respect d'un syst\u00e8me national de classification \u00e9labor\u00e9 en collaboration avec le Service canadien de la faune et les organismes provinciaux de la faune. Comme les autres secteurs, le secteur des ongul\u00e9s pr\u00e9sente sept classes. Outre la classe et la sous-classe, le syst\u00e8me indique l'esp\u00e8ce d'ongul\u00e9s \u00e0 laquelle renvoie la classification. Pour assurer la reproduction, la survie et la croissance des ongul\u00e9s, une zone g\u00e9ographique donn\u00e9e doit receler leurs nutriments en quantit\u00e9 et en qualit\u00e9 suffisantes, leur habitat et leur espace requis en quantit\u00e9s n\u00e9cessaires.  La cartographie des possibilit\u00e9s des terres pour la faune se fonde sur l'interpr\u00e9tation de cartes a\u00e9riennes et des r\u00e9sultats d'\u00e9tudes effectu\u00e9es sur le terrain. Des cotes d'aptitude sont \u00e9galement \u00e9tablies en fonction du couvert v\u00e9g\u00e9tal optimum qui peut \u00eatre maintenu gr\u00e2ce \u00e0 de bonnes pratiques de gestion de la faune.", "id": "003fadbe-f842-5705-9e9d-69bb43bef65d", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-126, 55], [-126, 56], [-124, 56], [-124, 55], [-126, 55]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/geott/cli_250k/ungulate/u093n.shp.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng", "format": "other"}], "browse_graphic_url": "http://www.fakeimageurl123.com/foo.jpg", "topic_category": "Biota  Biote", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "1972-01-01", "time_period_coverage_start": "", "data_series_name": "Canada Land Inventory (1:250,000) - Land Capability for Ungulates", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "", "notes": "The mapping of land capability for ungulates follows a national system developed with the aid of the Canadian Wildlife Service and the game branches of the provinces. The ungulate sector uses seven classes, like the others. In addition to class and subclass, the system indicates the ungulate species to which the classification refers. Capability for ungulate production implies a sufficient quantity and quality of food, protective cover, and space to meet the needs for survival, growth, and reproduction. Capability mapping is accomplished through interpretation of air photographs and by field surveys. Capability ratings are also established on the basis of the optimum vegetational stage that can be maintained with good wildlife management practices.", "title": "Canada La